reviews.text: Great atmosphere, average quality of food and coffee, I would say it’s overpriced (5 stars hotel price), probably because of the superior location.... Many better choices of cafes with relatively reasonable price in town ; )
A bit dim on the inside, pleasant sitting around outside. Good enough coffee, albeit quite expensive!

On my last morning in Hong Kong, the temperatures dropped but I dressed accurately - Not too warm, not too cold. I took a short stroll in the neighborhood and decided to sit at Lof10, since there were many happy dogs running around; the most I’ve seen since my arrival. I ordered a green tea cake and Matcha tea with whipped cream shaped like a swan. The mellow music made me cry and I wished I could go back home and still stay here.
